    "However, ANA detection in clinical practice is a typical multi-instance multi-label (MIML) task, which requires specialized algorithms.",
    "The differences between supervised learning, multi-instance learning, multilabel learning, and MIML are shown in Fig. 3.",
    "Among these, MIML is the most challenging because it combines the complexities of both multi-instance learning and multi-label learning.",
    "Zhou et al.",
    "proposed two approaches to solve MIML tasks by converting them into either multi-instance learning or multilabel learning tasks [29]."
